## Rich vs Anemic Comparison

### Anemic Model (Anti-Pattern)

```java
// Order.java - Just data, no behavior
public class Order {
    private UUID id;
    private OrderStatus status;
    private List<OrderLine> lines;
    
    // Getters and setters only...
}

// OrderService.java - All logic here
public class OrderService {
    public void placeOrder(UUID orderId) {
        Order order = repository.findById(orderId);
        if (order.getLines().isEmpty()) 
            throw new Exception("Empty order");
        order.setStatus(OrderStatus.PLACED);
        repository.save(order);
    }
}
```

### Rich Model (Correct)

```java
// Order.java - Data + Behavior
public class Order {
    private final UUID id;
    private OrderStatus status;
    private final List<OrderLine> lines;
    
    public void place() {
        if (lines.isEmpty()) throw new OrderException.EmptyOrder();
        this.status = OrderStatus.PLACED;
    }
}

// OrderService.java - Orchestration only
public class PlaceOrderUseCase {
    public OrderOutput execute(OrderInput input) {
        Order order = Order.create();
        // ...
        order.place();
        repository.save(order);
        return OrderOutput.from(order);
    }
}
```

